@startmindmap
* Voltaire (CIP-1694)
** Three bodies
*** Constitutional Committee (constitutionality)
*** DReps (ADA holders' voice)
*** SPOs (hard forks, some params)
** Seven action types
*** No-confidence
*** Update committee / threshold
*** New constitution / guardrails
*** Hard-fork initiation
*** Protocol parameter change
*** Treasury withdrawal
*** Info (non-binding)
** Ratification
*** Per-type threshold mix
*** Security params need extra SPO vote
*** Thresholds are governance-set
** Lifecycle
*** Live for govActionLifetime (6 epochs)
*** Ratified at epoch boundary
*** Enacted next boundary
*** Expired if thresholds unmet
** Participation
*** Register DRep (500 ADA deposit)
*** Delegate vote (separate from stake)
*** Abstain / No Confidence built-ins
*** Vote Yes / No / Abstain
*** Propose (refundable deposit)
** For developers
*** Governance = ordinary transactions
*** Params affect your contracts
*** Treasury funds development
*** Plutus V3 Voting / Proposing purposes
@endmindmap
